Context: The University of Toronto is a renowned institution with top faculty, students, alumni, and staff. One of its community members, David Dyzenhaus, was recognized with a Gold Medal from the Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council. In the latest issue of U of T Celebrates, topics include the role of electric vehicles in climate change, addiction treatments using AI and tech, and historical expeditions. The University operates on the traditional land of the Huron-Wendat, Seneca, and Mississaugas of the Credit. It was established in 1827.
